## Closures

A **closure** is the combination of a function and the lexical environment in which it was declared. The inner function keeps a live reference to the outer function's variables even after the outer function has returned.

```js
function makeCounter() {
  let count = 0;            // captured variable
  return function () {
    count += 1;            // still accessible
    return count;
  };
}

const next = makeCounter();
next(); // 1
next(); // 2
```

Closures power data privacy, function factories, memoization and event handlers.
